channel.description: Well I have just got a new computer right it is windows vista compaq.So my problem is my compiler doesn't work or my run.server.When I run my server:[font=Verdana]The system cannot find the path specified.[/font]When I run my compiler it says:[font=Verdana]You do not have jdk installed and load's the site.[/font]So I go and download java and now my java in program files looks like this: [img]http://img229.imageshack.us/img229/8058/1315kt0.jpg[/img].Jre 3 which is the newest java if im correct.So I go and change my enviromental varials which look's like this:[img]http://img185.imageshack.us/img185/3858/5i349693ko7.jpg[/img].So as you can see I have my CLASSPATH:C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_03\bin;%CLASSPATH%; and my PATH:C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_3\bin and at the bottem box(System Variables) I have my CLASSPATH:.;C:\Program Files\Java\jre1.6.0_03\lib\ext\QTJava.zip.So it looks all right I think?So now when I go to downlaod jdk 3 at http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp I accept click offline and in my sun download manager I click start download.So when I click it it fails and says this???: [img]http://img139.imageshack.us/img139/3491/jdkwc5.jpg[/img].If you can't see what it says it says:Failed to create file in destination directory.Help please?
